<item>
            <title>[SUREFIRE-52] XML Reports include testcases from previous tests</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SUREFIRE-52</link>
                <project id="12317927" key="SUREFIRE">Maven Surefire (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;to reproduce&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1. create the following JUnit tests:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;public class TestA extends TestCase {&lt;br/&gt;
   public void test1() {&lt;br/&gt;
   }&lt;br/&gt;
}&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;public class TestB extends TestCase {&lt;br/&gt;
   public void test2() {&lt;br/&gt;
}&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2. run &apos;mvn clean install&apos;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;note that in TEST-TestB.xml includes testcase results from test1 and test2, even though TestB only has test2()&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;testsuite errors=&quot;0&quot; skipped=&quot;0&quot; tests=&quot;1&quot; time=&quot;0&quot; failures=&quot;0&quot; name=&quot;TestB&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
...&lt;br/&gt;
  &amp;lt;testcase time=&quot;0&quot; name=&quot;test1&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
  &amp;lt;testcase time=&quot;0&quot; name=&quot;test2&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/testsuite&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
